{
  "texts": [
    "A larger population would provide a wider diversity of solutions, improving the chances of finding the WCET by exploring more of the solution space.",
    "However, it would also significantly increase the computational resources and time required for each generation.",
    "A population size of 100 is large enough to maintain a diverse set of solutions and provide a broad exploration of the search space, yet it remains computationally manageable.",
    "This size allows the algorithm to effectively search for the WCET without incurring prohibitive computational costs.In terms of fitness score in collision detection, if a collision happens, the execution time is assigned to be -1 to assign a negative reward for it.",
    "For reporting the results, the last generation of GA containing 100 individuals is stored."
  ]
}